abstract: Britain has formally left the European Union, but difficult trade talks remain before the two are severed.
snippet: Britain has formally left the European Union, but difficult trade talks remain before the two are severed.
lead_paragraph: Finally, after 1,317 days of confusion, rancor and endless votes in Parliament, it was time for Brexit. On Wednesday, teary members of the European Parliament joined hands and sang “Auld Lang Syne,” a clock projected onto 10 Downing Street counted down the minutes, Union Jacks lined the Mall before Buckingham Palace.

abstract: The Sanders online army resembles President Trump’s most ardent supporters in more ways than either side might care to admit.
snippet: The Sanders online army resembles President Trump’s most ardent supporters in more ways than either side might care to admit.
lead_paragraph: Barbara Boxer minces no words when it comes to describing the people usually known as the Bernie Bros — a subset of Bernie Sanders supporters who hope to take over the Democratic Party and remake it in their image.

headline_main: Once Skeptical, Senate Republicans Are All In on Trump
headline_print_headline: A Party Now Less Likely To Tell Trump ‘Enough’

abstract: The narrow vote came after Republican senators said they did not need to hear more evidence, and pressed toward acquitting President Trump next week.
snippet: The narrow vote came after Republican senators said they did not need to hear more evidence, and pressed toward acquitting President Trump next week.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate brought President Trump to the brink of acquittal on Friday of charges that he abused his power and obstructed Congress, as Republicans voted to block consideration of new witnesses and documents in his impeachment trial and shut down a final push by Democrats to bolster their case for the president’s removal.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The American ambassador whose abrupt recall from Ukraine helped lead to President Trump’s impeachment has retired from the State Department, a person familiar with her plans confirmed on Friday.

abstract: After a dramatic night and a day of expectation, the Senate voted in quick order to block Democratic calls for new witnesses and documents at President Donald Trump’s impeachment trial. The 51-49 vote Friday, just before the dinner hour Eastern time, all but ensures Trump's acquittal when senators answer the final impeachment roll call on Wednesday.
snippet: After a dramatic night and a day of expectation, the Senate voted in quick order to block Democratic calls for new witnesses and documents at President Donald Trump’s impeachment trial. The 51-49 vote Friday, just before the dinner hour Eastern ti...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — After a dramatic night and a day of expectation, the Senate voted in quick order to block Democratic calls for new witnesses and documents at President Donald Trump’s impeachment trial. The 51-49 vote Friday, just before the dinner hour Eastern time, all but ensures Trump's acquittal when senators answer the final impeachment roll call on Wednesday.
headline_main: Trial Highlights: After Drama, Quick Vote to Block Witnesses
headline_print_headline: Trial Highlights: After Drama, Quick Vote to Block Witnesses
